  "en_notes_asad": [
    {
      "note_no": "1",
      "note": "The term \"unlettered people\" (ummiyun) denotes a nation or community who had not previously had a revealed scripture of their own (Razi). The designation of the Prophet as a man \"from among themselves\" is meant, in this context, to stress the fact that he, too, was unlettered (ummi) in the primary sense of this word (cf. 7:157 and 158)., and could not, therefore, have \"invented\" the message of the Qur'an or \"derived\" its ideas from earlier scriptures."
    }
